<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-089-030  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 089 030.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Educational Technology  Jan 1990 v30 n1 p20(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Automating code generation for computer-based trainingdevelopment.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bryant, Robert A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>If a user has an authoring system that includes a programmablelanguage to develop courseware, automatically generating thesource code to drive the courseware is possible, to developcomputer-based training (CBT) development programs.andP;  Automaticcode generation will increase productivity and save on developmenttime and money.andP;  The staff of the Data Systems EngineeringOrganization (DSEO) at Marin Marietta Energy Systems Inc. workedfrom templates to develop a program generator capable ofgenerating code used for common functions, such as help screens;course, unit and lesson menus; review screens; and test screens.andO;Procedures for generating a program or lesson are included in thearticle, including examples.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Martin Marietta Energy Systems Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     Computer-Assisted InstructionCode GenerationProgram Development TechniquesEducationTrainingSource CodeCoursewareAuthoring.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>